title: Arrests made after legs of missing Hong Kong model found in fridge
description: The former in-laws of a Hong Kong model have been arrested on suspicion of murder after her legs were found in a fridge days after she went missing.

title: Ukraine stands firm a year into the fight - but the war is likely to grind on
description: Ukraine hopes to defeat Russia's invasion this year but, unless the West provides sufficient weapons to achieve a decisive victory or Vladimir Putin gives up, this war is set to grind on.

title: Ukrainians recite 'You'll Never Walk Alone' lyrics in powerful film to mark anniversary
description: The lyrics of "You'll Never Walk Alone" have been recited by Ukrainian people in a powerful film to mark the first anniversary of Russia's invasion.

title: 'All lives are priceless': Russian ambassador interrupts minute's silence for Ukraine
description: Russia's ambassador to the United Nations has interrupted a minute's silence for Ukraine as members of the Security Council stood up to honour the "victims of aggression" in the war.

title: A weeping widow says goodbye at her husband's grave in eastern Ukraine
description: In a windswept graveyard, Viktoria mourns her husband.

title: How this woman's trip from her grandmother's house changed her life forever
description: In May last year, we stood in the grounds of what had been a mass grave of the residents of Bucha - just a month after the city was liberated from invading Russian forces.

title: 'I'd rather die than go back': The remote Russian region with high casualties where an army contract is big money
description: Buryatia feels like it is a world away from war in Europe.

title: The unthinkable: What would Russian success in Ukraine mean for Western security?
description: President Vladimir Putin might have hoped for a swift and decisive invasion of Ukraine; instead, a year on, Russia has paid a huge price for his imperial ambition.

title: One year of civilian life on the frontline of Ukraine's war
description: When Russia invaded Ukraine on 24 February 2022, Sky News set out to find Ukrainians who could document their experiences as war twisted their lives out of shape.

title: Bird flu infections in humans 'still rare' despite Cambodian girl's death
description: The world is on high alert for human cases of bird flu.

title: Netflix cuts prices in more than 30 countries in bid to win more subscribers
description: Netflix has cut its prices in more than 30 countries, in some cases slashing the price of a subscription in half.

title: China unveils 12-point peace plan to solve Ukraine war
description: China has called for a ceasefire and peace talks in Ukraine on the first anniversary of the Russian invasion.

title: 'He kept shooting at me': Photographer at scene of Florida shooting describes moment his colleague was killed
description: A photographer has described the moment his journalist colleague was killed in a Florida shooting, which left him wounded and a nine-year-old girl and a woman dead.

title: Private equity pioneer Thomas Lee dies from 'self-inflicted gunshot wound'
description: A billionaire financier, considered a pioneer of private equity investment, has been found dead in his New York office after reportedly taking his own life.

title: Los Angeles has first blizzard warning in decades
description: A blizzard warning has been issued for Los Angeles for the first time in more than three decades.

title: 'We remain invincible': Ukraine leader pledges push for victory on war anniversary
description: Ukrainians have proven themselves to be "invincible", Volodymyr Zelenskyy has said, as he attended a memorial service out in the open in central Kyiv - marking a year since Russia's invasion of Ukraine.

title: Vladimir Putin will be on trial for war crimes one day, US envoy warns
description: It is only a matter of time before Vladimir Putin is on trial for war crimes according to President Biden's envoy for global criminal justice.

title: Counting the cost: This is how many civilians have lost their lives in the first year of the war
description: They are mundane locations: a garage, a sports hall, a nursery, farm buildings, a bus stop. All have been attacked in the last week in Ukraine.
